         projects from different organizations.
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>
            FALSE POSITIVE: CVE-2026-42154 targets the Prometheus server
            (prometheus/prometheus on GitHub). OWASP incorrectly matches it against
            micrometer-registry-prometheus via CPE name similarity. Micrometer is a
            metrics facade by the Spring team — not the Prometheus server.
        </notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/io\.micrometer/micrometer\-registry\-prometheus@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-42154</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         io.netty:* (any module) — CVE-2026-42582
         VERDICT: FALSE POSITIVE (wrong module + already-fixed version)

         CVE-2026-42582 affects netty-codec-http3, a module this project does
         not depend on (no HTTP/3 usage — this is a Kafka/Spring Boot backend).

         OWASP maps every io.netty:* artifact to the same broad CPE
         cpe:2.3:a:netty:netty:<version>, with no module-level distinction.
         CVE-2026-42582's NVD configuration matches this broad CPE regardless
         of version — netty-transport@4.1.135.Final, then
         netty-transport-native-unix-common@4.1.135.Final, and now
         netty-codec@4.1.135.Final have each in turn been flagged with the
         identical CVE as NVD data refreshed, even though 4.1.135.Final is
         already past the 4.1.133.Final release that fixed this CVE upstream.

         Narrower regexes (netty-transport@.*, then netty-transport.*@.*) were
         tried first but this is whack-a-mole: Netty has dozens of modules
         (netty-buffer, netty-common, netty-handler, netty-resolver, ...) and
         any of them can be the one that surfaces in dependency:tree after the
         next NVD refresh. Widened to the full io.netty groupId — this project
         doesn't use netty-codec-http3 regardless of which sibling module NVD
         maps the CVE onto next.

         Tracked upstream: dependency-check/DependencyCheck#8576 (Netty CVEs
         mismatched across sibling modules via the shared broad CPE).
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <suppress until="2026-12-31Z">
        <notes>
            FALSE POSITIVE: CVE-2026-42582 affects netty-codec-http3, which this
            project does not use (no HTTP/3). OWASP maps every io.netty:*
            artifact to the same broad cpe:2.3:a:netty:netty:* CPE with no
            module distinction — netty-transport, then
            netty-transport-native-unix-common, then netty-codec have each been
            flagged in turn at 4.1.135.Final, already past the 4.1.133.Final fix.
            Widened to the whole io.netty groupId to stop the whack-a-mole across
            Netty's dozens of modules. Tracked upstream:
            dependency-check/DependencyCheck#8576
        </notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/io\.netty/.*@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-42582</cve>
    </suppress>

